parse: Verb - Imperfect Indicative Middle or Passive - 3rd Person Singular
str2: (a) I am powerful, have (the) power, (b) I am able, I can. Of uncertain affinity; to be able or possible.
From apo and krino; to conclude for oneself, i.e. to respond; by Hebraism to begin to speak.
From lego; something said; by implication, a topic, also reasoning or motive; by extension, a computation; specially, the Divine Expression.
Neither, nor, not even, and not. From ou and de; not however, i.e. Neither, nor, not even.
From, away from. A primary particle; 'off, ' i.e. Away, in various senses.
That, that one there, yonder. From ekei; that one (neuter) thing); often intensified by the article prefixed.
A day, the period from sunrise to sunset.

parse: Interrogative / Indefinite Pronoun - Nominative Masculine Singular
str2: Any one, some one, a certain one or thing. An enclitic indefinite pronoun; some or any person or object.

parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: To dare, endure, be bold, have courage, make up the mind. From tolma; to venture; by implication, to be courageous.
To interrogate, question, demand of. From epi and erotao; to ask for, i.e. Inquire, seek.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Accusative Masculine 3rd Person Singular
str2: He, she, it, they, them, same. From the particle au; the reflexive pronoun self, used of the third person, and of the other persons.
No longer, no more. Also ouk eti from ou and eti; not yet, no longer.
